						<summary>

						<p>Nandi pillar set up near the northern <hi rend="italic">gōpura</hi> out side the Mallikārjuna temple.</p>						

						<p>This undated epigraph may be assigned to the 16th-17th century, on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>It states the erection of a lamp-post <hi rend="italic">(Dīpa-kamba)</hi> by a person named Kalyāṇam Ārya.</p>						

						</summary>
